The article discusses the economic approach of President Biden, known as Bidenomics, which aims to move away from trickle-down economics and focus on growing the economy from the middle class and bottom up. The core idea behind Bidenomics is to make targeted public investments in sectors that are important for long-term economic and national security interests, such as infrastructure, semiconductors, clean energy, and climate security. The article highlights that this approach has already led to a resurgence in American manufacturing, with a significant increase in construction of manufacturing facilities in the US. Bidenomics is also driving investments in semiconductors, electric vehicles, clean energy, and infrastructure projects across the country.